ek Ramaswamy wins GOP nomination for governor in Ohio</title><updateDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 23:38:54 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Henry J. Gomez</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 05 May 2026 23:38:01 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Former Sen. Sherrod Brown has won the Democratic nomination in Ohio’s special Senate election, NBC News projects, paving the way for a nationally watched general election matchup against Republican incumbent Jon Husted</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/sherrod-brown-wins-ohio-senate-democratic-primary-jon-husted-rcna343049</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/sherrod-brown-wins-ohio-senate-democratic-primary-jon-husted-rcna343049</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-08/250815-sherrod-brown-se-253p-d1585c.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Michael Brochstein</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Sherrod Brown. speaking during a news conference</media:text><media:description type="plain">Sherrod Brown is running for Senate again in 2026 after losing in 2024.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-08/250815-sherrod-brown-se-253p-d1585c.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 23:38:01 GMT</pubDate><title>Sherrod Brown wins Democratic Senate nomination in Ohio, setting up a key battleground race</title><updateDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 23:38:01 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Lauren Dunn</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 05 May 2026 23:10:11 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The WHO said that some passengers aboard the MV Hondius cruise ship may have been infected with the deadly hantavirus through extremely rare person-to-person transmission.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/hantavirus-outbreak-mv-hondius-cruise-ship-who-expert-explains-rcna343467</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/hantavirus-outbreak-mv-hondius-cruise-ship-who-expert-explains-rcna343467</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260504-hondius-cruise-ship-mb-1118-881a58.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>AFP via Getty Images</media:credit><media:text type="plain">An outbreak of &#34;severe acute respiratory illness&#34; on board a cruise ship in the Atlantic has left two people dead and a third in intensive care in Johannesburg.</media:text><media:description type="plain">The MV Hondius cruise ship off the port of Praia, Cape Verde on May 3, 2026. </media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260504-hondius-cruise-ship-mb-1118-881a58.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 23:10:11 GMT</pubDate><title>How hantavirus spreads: What to know about rare person-to-person transmission</title><updateDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 23:10:11 GMT</updateDate></item></channel></rss>